<p>
The <code>handleActivationRequest</code> function is a wrapper for the <a href="/docs/(Node) handleAPIRequest">handleAPIRequest</a> function that only accepts requests from MinoCloud to activate the <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a>. The function uses the request and response objects used by the node module <a href="http://expressjs.com">Express.js</a>. It should be used on an address (Express route) that you designate as the <code>Activation URL</code>.
</p>

<div class="heading">handleActivationRequest(<code>request</code>,<code>response</code>,<code>callback</code>)</div>
<p>
<code>request</code><br />
<code>Type: Express Request</code><br />
The <a target="_blank" href="http://expressjs.com">Express</a> request object.
</p>
<p>
<code>response</code><br />
<code>Type: Express Response</code><br />
The <a target="_blank" href="http://expressjs.com">Express</a> response object.
</p>
<p>
<code>callback</code><br />
<code>Type: Function(appUser,respond)</code><br />
A function that will be called with the username of the new user as <code>appUser</code>.
<br />
<br />
The <code>callback</code> function is where the <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a> should perform the actions necessary to make the <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a> work for the new user.
<br />
<br />
<code>appUser</code> is the end-user of the <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a> that this request is for.
<br />
<br />
<code>respond</code> is the function that your <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a> should use to output the result of the activation attempt. Returning <code>true</code> is the only response that will result in a successful activation.
</p>

<div class="heading">Example Usage</div>
<p>
If the <code>request</code> includes a URL parameter named <code>minocloud_session_cookie</code> then this value will be set as the cookie and a "Location" header will be sent. This will end the request and the <code>callback</code> will not be called.
</p>
<pre>
var minocloud = new MinoCloud("ExampleApp","3XaMpL3ApPaP1K3Y");

minocloud.handleActivationRequest(
  request,
  response,
  function(appUser,respond){
    /* Save any folders that the app is going to use
     * for this user's data then respond with true. */
    respond(true);
  }
);
</pre>

<p>
Using <code>respond()</code> with any parameter other than <code>true</code> will cause an error in the activation process and the value returned will be shown so that you can debug the activation procedure for your <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a>.
</p>